# Trivy ignore file for the turma-agent + turma image scans
# (.github/workflows/turma-agent-image-scan.yml, turma-image-scan.yml).
#
# Only REVIEWED, non-actionable findings belong here, each with a reason. Any
# HIGH/CRITICAL not listed here still fails the scan — this is a triage list,
# not a mute button. Revisit entries when the upstream fix reaches our base image.

# CVE-2026-39822 — Go stdlib os.Root symlink-following / directory-traversal.
# Present only in bundled third-party Go binaries (docker CLI 29.6.1, gh 2.96.0
# and terraform 1.15.8), compiled with Go 1.26.4 / 1.25.10; the fix is Go
# 1.25.12 / 1.26.5. All three are already the newest upstream releases (docker
# 29.6.1 2026-06-26, gh 2.96.0 2026-07-02, terraform 1.15.8), so
# DOCKER_CLI_VERSION / GH_VERSION / TERRAFORM_VERSION can't be bumped yet —
# they'll pick up the patched toolchain on their next rebuild. Not first-party
# code and not reachable via attacker-controlled symlinks in this container. The
# expiry forces a revisit: bump the pins once upstream ships Go-1.26.5+ rebuilds.
CVE-2026-39822 exp:2026-10-10

# CVE-2026-27145 / CVE-2026-42504 — Go stdlib DoS: unbounded work parsing a
# crafted x509 DNS name / MIME header. Both reach us only through terraform
# 1.15.8's own Go 1.25.10 build (fix: Go 1.25.11+), and 1.15.8 IS the latest
# terraform, so TERRAFORM_VERSION has nothing to bump to — the next HashiCorp
# release built on a patched toolchain clears both. Third-party, and a DoS
# against a CLI that a session runs by hand against certs and metadata it
# already chose to fetch: the blast radius is that one terraform invocation.
# Expiry forces the revisit.
CVE-2026-27145 exp:2026-10-10
CVE-2026-42504 exp:2026-10-10

# GHSA-537c-gmf6-5ccf — the cryptography wheel bundles a vulnerable OpenSSL.
# From azure-cli's OWN vendored python (/opt/az, cryptography 46.0.7; fixed in
# 48.0.1), not anything this repo installs — az ships and pins that tree itself,
# so the only lever here is AZURE_CLI_VERSION, and 2.88.0 is already the newest
# package Microsoft publishes for bookworm. Revisit on the expiry: a later
# azure-cli vendoring cryptography 48+ clears it with a pin bump.
GHSA-537c-gmf6-5ccf exp:2026-10-10
